# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback for dedicated artwork URLs.
#
# This is a single-file static site — there is no real file at
# /artwork/123, /artwork/456, etc. Without this rule, visiting one of
# those URLs directly (a shared link, or a search engine crawling the
# <a href="/artwork/{id}"> links rendered in the gallery) would 404.
#
# This rule tells Cloudflare Pages to serve index.html for any
# /artwork/* path while keeping the URL in the browser's address bar
# unchanged (status 200, not a redirect). index.html's own JS then
# reads the id from the URL on load and opens the matching artwork's
# modal + SEO metadata (see openArtworkById() in the main script).
/artwork/*  /index.html  200

# Sitemap and robots.txt are real files / a Pages Function and are
# NOT covered by the catch-all above, so they keep being served
# directly and are not redirected to index.html.
